title.en: Heroes of the Storm: HGC EU Summer Regional 2016

desc.en: With the Heroes of the Storm Summer Regional right here you can relive the best of the best. This match-up is between Dignitas and Team Sandwich Monkeys.

We are bringing together some of the best voices in competitive Heroes of the Storm to entertain you with Heroes of the Storm action from Cologne, Germany. 100.000 US dollars is the prize pool spread between the top four best teams. The participating teams are Team Dignitas, Misfits, Fanatic, ExcelenteEleccion, To Be Determined, Too far bjutifl for 640x480, ePunks and GoodlelshetZont.

title.en: Heroes of the Storm: HGC Gamescom 2016

desc.en: Eight teams from around the world gathered in Katowice, Poland in order to fight for their share of a minimum 100.000 dollars prize pool as well as the prestigious title and trophy, and none of them were willing to give up their chance without a fight. This game is between ESC Ever and Team SoloMid.

The 12 best teams from North America and Europe (6 from each region) will compete in a three-day tournament to determine the best Vainglory team in the West. Going on from May 19-21. See all the pros play in front of a live audience, at the legendary O2 in London, UK. The 2017 Spring Championship is the first time both NA and EU teams will compete at the same regional championship

title.en: Heroes of the Storm: HGC NA Summer Regional 2016

desc.en: World of Esports is the place to catch up on the latest and best from the world of esports. From CS:GO, to League of Legends and Rocket League, EsportsCenter brings news, interviews, plays of the week and much more in this brand new show, which aims to provide exceptional insight into the world of competitive gaming. Featuring host OJ Borg.

Intel Extreme Masters will visit Katowice for the fifth year in a row. In March 2017, IEM will bring the best gaming action to the Spodek Arena with Counter-Strike: Global Offensive. The tournaments that take the stage in Katowice feature the world's most talented progamers. The participating teams are Astralis, Fnatic, Heroic, Immortals, Natus Vincere, North, FaZe Clan, Cloud9, Ninjas in Pyjamas, OpTic Gaming, SK Gaming, Virtus.pro. These gamers will fight for the World Championship title and a prize pool of $650,000 USD. This match is from the Grand Final.
